<!-- WOW: Eastern Ukraine industrial profile -->
<section class="dn-sec"><div class="ctr">
  <div class="dn-chip dn-chip-dark">EASTERN UKRAINE INDUSTRIAL PROFILE</div>
  <h2 class="dn-h2">Why Dnipro region matters for international e-commerce serving Ukraine</h2>
  <p class="dn-lede">If you're an international brand evaluating Ukrainian market entry, Dnipropetrovsk Oblast is one of three regions you must serve well — alongside Kyiv and Lviv regions. It's industrial heartland with above-average median income and strong B2B distribution capacity. Below — concrete data points.</p>
  <div class="dn-profile-grid">
    <div class="dn-profile-card">
      <h3>Demographics &amp; income</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Population:</strong> 3.0M (Dnipropetrovsk Oblast)</li>
        <li><strong>Major cities:</strong> Dnipro 1.0M, Kryvyi Rih 640K, Kamianske 240K, Nikopol 110K, Pavlohrad 105K</li>
        <li><strong>Median income:</strong> $720/month (above Ukrainian national average)</li>
        <li><strong>Urbanization:</strong> 84% urban, 16% rural — high concentration around Dnipro and Kryvyi Rih</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="dn-profile-card">
      <h3>E-commerce profile</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Market rank:</strong> 4th largest UA e-commerce region by GMV (after Kyiv, Lviv, Odesa)</li>
        <li><strong>Carrier preference:</strong> 24% Nova Poshta express, 31% NP standard, 18% Ukrposhta, rest local courier</li>
        <li><strong>B2B distribution hub:</strong> automotive parts, industrial equipment, cosmetics</li>
        <li><strong>Marketplace usage:</strong> Rozetka 42%, Prom 38%, Kasta 12% (similar to national)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="dn-profile-card">
      <h3>Logistics coverage</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Nova Poshta:</strong> 120+ branches in Dnipro city, 250+ self-service lockers across region</li>
        <li><strong>Same-day pickup:</strong> at our Kyiv warehouse → next-day Dnipro delivery (NP express)</li>
        <li><strong>Direct courier:</strong> NP courier addresses in Dnipro city +1 day from branch delivery</li>
        <li><strong>Returns:</strong> any NP branch in region → back to Kyiv warehouse 1-2 days</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div></section>

<!-- WHY KYIV BEATS LOCAL DNIPRO WAREHOUSE -->
<section class="dn-sec dn-sec-light"><div class="ctr">
  <div class="dn-chip dn-chip-dark">KYIV HUB ARGUMENT</div>
  <h2 class="dn-h2">Why a single Kyiv hub serves Dnipro region better than a local Dnipro warehouse</h2>
  <div class="dn-prob-grid">
    <div class="dn-prob-card">
      <div class="dn-prob-num">70-80%</div>
      <h3>Most customers are not in Dnipro</h3>
      <p>For brands selling across Ukraine, only 20-30% of buyers from Dnipro-region merchants live in Dnipro itself. The 70-80% majority is scattered across Kyiv, Lviv, Odesa, and smaller cities. Kyiv hub is geographically closer to that majority via Nova Poshta network. A local Dnipro warehouse would only be faster for the local 20-30% — the rest would slow down.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="dn-prob-card">
      <div class="dn-prob-num">MARKETS</div>
      <h3>Marketplace logistics centers are in Kyiv</h3>
      <p>Rozetka Marketplace, Prom.ua, Kasta head offices and main sorting centers are in Kyiv. Our Kyiv warehouse sits on the same logistics routes — escalations and issue resolution happen faster than from a peripheral Dnipro location. For international sellers using these marketplaces, Kyiv warehouse is the natural fulfillment node.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="dn-prob-card">
      <div class="dn-prob-num">RISK</div>
      <h3>War-resilience favors Kyiv geographically</h3>
      <p>Kyiv has been operationally stable since February 2022 with 0 days of MTP fulfillment downtime. We run 3 backup generators, dual fiber + Starlink internet, 7-day fuel reserves. Dnipro is closer to risk lines and has experienced more frequent infrastructure disruptions. For international brands, Kyiv hub offers structurally lower operational risk than a Dnipro hub would.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="dn-prob-card">
      <div class="dn-prob-num">COST</div>
      <h3>Single hub eliminates fixed-cost duplication</h3>
      <p>Operating two warehouses (Kyiv + Dnipro) for Ukrainian e-commerce means double rent, double staff, double WMS overhead. Single Kyiv hub serves all of Ukraine via Nova Poshta with 1-2 day transit to any region. Per-order cost stays at $0.41 instead of fragmenting inventory across regions.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="dn-prob-card">
      <div class="dn-prob-num">EXPORT</div>
      <h3>Cross-border exits are in Kyiv area</h3>
      <p>Nova Poshta International, Meest, and DHL hub locations cluster around Kyiv-Boryspil airport and Kyiv ground transport hubs. For brands selling to EU diaspora or international markets, Kyiv warehouse is closer to exit points than Dnipro. Cross-border parcels save 1-2 days transit when sent from Kyiv vs Dnipro.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="dn-prob-card">
      <div class="dn-prob-num">SCALE</div>
      <h3>Single hub scales 30→6000 orders/day</h3>
      <p>Our Kyiv facility handles 60,000 shipments per month with capacity to grow. Same per-order tariff applies whether you ship 30 or 6,000 daily — no fixed-cost step changes. Dnipro-region merchants joining MTP plug into the same operational scale as Kyiv-based merchants. No premium for non-Kyiv origin.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div></section>

<!-- COVERAGE -->
