<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="dn-sec dn-sec-light" id="dn-cta"><div class="ctr">
  <div class="dn-chip dn-chip-dark">FREQUENTLY ASKED</div>
  <h2 class="dn-h2">Questions international brands ask about Dnipro region fulfillment</h2>
  <div class="dn-faq">
    <details><summary>Why a Kyiv warehouse instead of a Dnipro warehouse for Eastern Ukraine?</summary><p>For brands selling across all of Ukraine, Kyiv is the optimal hub. 70-80% of customers are not in Dnipro — they're scattered across the country. Kyiv warehouse is geographically closer to that majority via Nova Poshta network. Plus war-resilience (0 days down since Feb 2022), proximity to marketplace logistics centers, and direct access to international exit points.</p></details>
    <details><summary>How long does delivery take from Kyiv warehouse to Dnipro Ukraine?</summary><p>1-2 business days standard via Nova Poshta. Order placed by 14:00 → picked at our Kyiv warehouse in 47 seconds → final pickup 17:00 → overnight Poltava sorting center → arrives Dnipro NP branch 8 AM next day → customer collects 10 AM. Total cycle 24 hours. NP carrier cost $1.50-2.50 per parcel depending on weight/tier.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Do you have a physical warehouse in Dnipro?</summary><p>No. We operate exclusively from our Kyiv-area facilities (Shchaslyve 2,700 m² + Bilohorodka 1,000 m²). We don't pretend to have a Dnipro warehouse. Single Kyiv hub serves Dnipro region merchants better than a local Dnipro warehouse would for cross-Ukraine distribution.</p></details>
    <details><summary>How does war affect Kyiv vs Dnipro fulfillment reliability?</summary><p>Kyiv has been operationally stable since February 2022 with 0 days of MTP fulfillment downtime. Backup generators, dual fiber + Starlink, 7-day fuel reserves. Dnipro is closer to risk lines with more frequent infrastructure disruptions. Kyiv hub offers materially lower operational risk for international brands.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What is Eastern Ukraine market like for international e-commerce?</summary><p>Dnipropetrovsk Oblast = 3.0M population, 4th largest UA e-commerce region by GMV. Median income $720/month above national average. Strong B2B distribution market. 24% prefer Nova Poshta express delivery. Strong marketplace usage (Rozetka 42%, Prom 38%, Kasta 12%).</p></details>
    <details><summary>Which marketplaces and platforms integrate with Kyiv hub for Dnipro region?</summary><p>All major UA platforms (Rozetka, Prom, Kasta, Allo, Horoshop) plus international (Shopify, WooCommerce, Etsy, Amazon Seller Central, BigCommerce, Magento) via REST API. Same integration regardless of customer destination region.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What is the pricing model?</summary><p>$0.41 per order at 200+ daily volume, $0.50-0.59 at 30-200 daily, plus storage and per-shipment Nova Poshta carrier rates. Min monthly fee $120 (5,000 UAH) for first 3 months. No premium for Eastern Ukraine destinations.</p></details>
    <details><summary>How fast can we onboard?</summary><p>3-5 business days for catalogs under 1,000 SKU. Inbound inventory ships to our Kyiv warehouse, gets slotted in WMS, API integration takes 2 hours, end-to-end test order before go-live.</p></details>
  </div>
</div></section>

<!-- TYPICAL ONBOARDING SCENARIOS -->
<section class="dn-sec dn-sec-light"><div class="ctr">
  <div class="dn-chip dn-chip-dark">ONBOARDING SCENARIOS</div>
  <h2 class="dn-h2">Three typical onboarding patterns for international brands serving Dnipro region from our Kyiv hub</h2>
  <p class="dn-lede">No invented numbers. Three real scenarios we've seen with international brands using our Kyiv warehouse to serve Eastern Ukrainian customers including Dnipro. Anonymized patterns without revealing specific brands.</p>
  <div class="dn-prob-grid">
    <div class="dn-prob-card">
      <div class="dn-prob-num">CASE 1</div>
      <h3>EU fashion brand 50-100 orders/day</h3>
      <p>European Shopify-based fashion brand entering Ukrainian market via Rozetka Marketplace and own DTC site. Wanted Eastern Ukraine reach but no local entity. Onboarding: 7 days end-to-end. Inbound 2 SKU pallets via standard freight forwarder Berlin→Kyiv (8 days transit). API integration with Shopify took 3 hours. First orders to Dnipro and Kryvyi Rih within day 8. Cost savings vs running own Eastern Ukraine warehouse: prevented entirely (avoided $40K setup + $5K/month operational).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="dn-prob-card">
      <div class="dn-prob-num">CASE 2</div>
      <h3>US D2C cosmetics brand 200+ orders/day</h3>
      <p>US-based clean beauty brand with growing Eastern European demand. Tested cross-border shipping from US warehouse — too slow (14-21 days), too expensive ($8-15/order). Onboarded MTP for Ukraine market specifically. Transit US→Kyiv warehouse via DHL 6 days. Then Kyiv→Dnipro 1-2 days. Per-order cost dropped from $14 to $0.41 + $1.80 NP = under $2.50 total. Volume tripled within 3 months as price-sensitive Eastern Ukrainian customers became reachable.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="dn-prob-card">
      <div class="dn-prob-num">CASE 3</div>
      <h3>Etsy seller 30-80 orders/day</h3>
      <p>Independent craft seller from Czech Republic with Ukrainian customer interest including Dnipro region buyers. Pre-MTP: each Ukraine order took 14-21 days transit and $12-18 shipping. With MTP: ships single inventory pool to Kyiv warehouse via Czech Post freight (12 days, batch monthly). From Kyiv to any Ukraine including Dnipro: 1-2 days, $1.80 NP cost. Customer satisfaction improved (faster delivery), seller margin improved (lower per-order cost), Etsy listing prominence improved (faster shipping rating).</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div></section>

<!-- OPERATIONS DEEP DIVE -->
<section class="dn-sec"><div class="ctr">
  <div class="dn-chip dn-chip-dark">OPERATIONS WORKFLOW</div>
  <h2 class="dn-h2">How an international brand serves Dnipro region from our Kyiv hub — step by step</h2>
  <p class="dn-lede">No black box: literal workflow showing how international brand's order to a Dnipro customer flows through our Kyiv warehouse. Each step measured, logged in WMS, auditable.</p>
  <ol class="dn-flow">
    <li><strong>Onboarding integration (days 1-2).</strong> We connect to your Shopify, WooCommerce, Etsy, Amazon Seller Central, or custom platform via REST API. Your store keeps running as-is — only change is order data now flows to our WMS instead of your previous fulfillment provider.</li>
    <li><strong>Inbound inventory shipment (days 2-7).</strong> You ship product to our Kyiv warehouse (Shchaslyve facility, address provided at contract). EU brands typically use standard freight forwarders — transit 5-10 days. US brands ship via DHL or FedEx air freight 4-6 days. We receive, verify against packing list, photo-document condition.</li>
    <li><strong>WMS slotting (days 7-9).</strong> Each SKU gets bin location on shelves via slotting algorithm. Hot-velocity items near pack station, long-tail items in deeper aisles. Bulky/heavy items in dedicated zones. Address-storage means pickers walk to specific bins, never search by memory.</li>
    <li><strong>Dashboard access (day 9).</strong> You get 24/7 WMS dashboard from anywhere globally. Real-time stock levels, order status pipeline, returns log, financial reports. API webhooks for status changes (new → picked → shipped → delivered).</li>
    <li><strong>End-to-end test order (days 9-10).</strong> We place test order to a Ukrainian address (often Dnipro for Eastern Ukraine validation). Verify full cycle: pick at Kyiv warehouse, barcode scan verification, packing with QC checkpoint, Nova Poshta label generation, dispatch, delivery confirmation at Dnipro NP branch. Pass = go-live.</li>
    <li><strong>Production operations (day 11+).</strong> Orders flow automatically from your platform. We pick in 47 seconds (avg 3-4 SKU order), pack with two-stage scan verification, QC checkpoint for high-value or multi-SKU orders, label and ship via 4 daily Nova Poshta pickups. Shipped status syncs back to your platform via API.</li>
    <li><strong>Inventory replenishment.</strong> When SKU stock drops below your defined threshold, dashboard alerts you and your operations team. You ship replenishment via standard freight to our Kyiv warehouse. Same receiving protocol — verify, photo-document, slot in WMS, available for orders within 24 hours of arrival.</li>
    <li><strong>Returns processing.</strong> Customer drops off return at any Nova Poshta branch in Dnipro or anywhere in Ukraine. Parcel returns to our Kyiv warehouse in 1-2 days. We receive, photo-document condition, verify completeness, return to shelf (if OK) or quarantine zone (if damaged). Returns report in your dashboard same day.</li>
  </ol>
</div></section>

<!-- SEO CLOSING -->
<section class="dn-sec dn-sec-light"><div class="ctr">
  <h2 class="dn-h2">Eastern Ukraine fulfillment without Dnipro warehouse — structural Kyiv hub advantage</h2>
  <p>We're transparent about our setup: MTP operates exclusively from Kyiv-area facilities (Shchaslyve 2,700 m² + Bilohorodka 1,000 m²). We don't have a Dnipro warehouse and we don't pretend to. Our argument to international brands evaluating Ukrainian market: a single Kyiv hub serves Dnipro region better than a local Dnipro warehouse would for cross-Ukraine distribution.</p>
  <p>Three reasons. First, geography: 70-80% of Ukrainian e-commerce customers are not in Dnipro — they're in Kyiv, Lviv, Odesa, smaller cities, rural areas. Kyiv warehouse is closer to that majority via Nova Poshta network. A local Dnipro warehouse would only be faster for the local 20-30%. Second, marketplace logistics: Rozetka, Prom, Kasta, Allo head offices and sorting centers cluster in Kyiv area. International brands using these platforms benefit from same-route operations. Third, war-resilience: Kyiv has been operationally stable since February 2022 with 0 days down, while Dnipro is closer to risk lines with more frequent disruptions.</p>
  <p>Cost economics favor single Kyiv hub too. Operating two regional warehouses (Kyiv + Dnipro) doubles rent, staff, WMS overhead. Single hub serves all of Ukraine with 1-2 day transit via Nova Poshta. Per-order cost stays at $0.41 instead of fragmenting inventory across regions. International brands using MTP don't pay premium for Eastern Ukraine destinations — same rate as for any Ukrainian zone.</p>
  <p>Dnipropetrovsk Oblast is concrete and worth serving: 3.0M population, 4th largest UA e-commerce GMV, $720/month median income (above national average), strong B2B distribution market for automotive parts and industrial equipment. International brands targeting Eastern Ukraine industrial/consumer markets get full coverage from our Kyiv hub via Nova Poshta network — without needing local Dnipro presence.</p>
  <p>See also: <a href="/en/fulfillment-ukraine/">fulfillment across Ukraine</a>, <a href="/en/calculator/">pricing calculator</a>, <a href="/en/services/">full services portfolio</a>, <a href="/en/order-pick-and-pack-ukraine/">order pick and pack details</a>, <a href="/en/3pl/">3PL logistics overview</a>.</p>
</div></section>

